The "Refused to display... X-Frame-Options" error typically occurs when an application tries to navigate the top-level window or change the URL fragment (hash) in a way that the hosting environment (AI Studio's iframe) blocks for security reasons.

When you click on a section link in the sidebar, the default behavior of the anchor tag (`<a href="#section-name">`) attempts to update the URL hash. The hosting sandbox likely prevents this navigation event, throwing the error you see in the console.

I will fix this by preventing the default anchor navigation and using JavaScript's `scrollIntoView` method to smoothly scroll to the section instead. This stays within the page context and won't trigger the iframe security blocking.

# Updated files:

## pages/Exam.tsx

Updated the sidebar navigation links to prevent default browser navigation (URL hash updates), which was causing "X-Frame-Options" errors in the AI Studio environment. Instead, it now uses `scrollIntoView` for smooth, error-free scrolling. Also ensured the `ref` callback correctly returns `void` to satisfy TypeScript.

