The "Refused to display... X-Frame-Options" error happens because standard anchor links (`<a href="#section">`) attempt to update the browser's URL hash. In the secure AI Studio iframe environment, this navigation event is blocked, causing the error and preventing the scroll.

The fix is to intercept the click event on these links, prevent the default browser navigation, and handle the scrolling programmatically using JavaScript.

The `editor.main.js` errors you are seeing are likely coming from the AI Studio environment itself (which uses the Monaco Editor) or a browser extension, as your application code uses PrismJS (`components/CodeRunner.tsx`) and not Monaco Editor. These warnings can be safely ignored as they don't affect your app's functionality.

