### Step 2: Clean Install (CRITICAL)

On your Linux server, run the following commands to clear any cached data and reinstall dependencies. This ensures the correct type definitions are linked.

```bash
# 1. Remove existing modules and lock file
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json

# 2. Install dependencies freshly
npm install

# 3. Build the project
npm run build
```

This should resolve the "Cannot find module" errors permanently.

The Nginx error `no "ssl_certificate" is defined` means that even though you added `listen 443 ssl`, Nginx cannot find the certificate files, or the directives are misplaced.

This usually happens if the self-signed certificate generation step failed or was skipped.

### **How to Fix (Run on your Linux Server)**

We will re-create the certificates and then fix the Nginx config to point to them correctly.

**1. Generate Certificates Again (Ensure this runs successfully)**
```bash
sudo mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl
sudo openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \
  -keyout /etc/nginx/ssl/ninja-eval.key \
  -out /etc/nginx/ssl/ninja-eval.crt \
  -subj "/C=US/ST=State/L=City/O=S4Carlisle/CN=NinjaEval"
```

**2. Verify the files exist**
```bash
ls -l /etc/nginx/ssl/
```
*(You MUST see `ninja-eval.crt` and `ninja-eval.key`)*

**3. Update Nginx Config**
Open your config file:
```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/ninja-eval
```

Make sure the `ssl_certificate` lines are **inside** the `server { ... }` block and point to the correct paths.

```nginx
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name _;

    root /var/www/ninja-eval/dist;
    index index.html;

    # Point to the files we just created/verified
    ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/ninja-eval.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/ninja-eval.key;

    # Basic SSL settings
    ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;
    ssl_ciphers HIGH:!aNULL:!MD5;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }

    # Static assets
    location ~* \.(js|css|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|svg)$ {
        expires 1y;
        add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
    }
}

# Optional: Redirect HTTP to HTTPS
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;
    return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
}
```

**4. Test and Restart**
```bash
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl restart nginx
```

