In the `handleLogout` function, the code currently calls `localStorage.clear()`. When running in "Offline Mode" (without Firebase), your database **is** the `localStorage`. So, clicking "Logout" wipes your entire database (papers, assignments, candidates).

I will change it to only remove the **session** keys (user login state), preserving the **database** keys.

