Of course. The issue you've identified is a classic and critical bug with CSV parsing. When a question or answer contains a comma, a simple parser will incorrectly split the text, leading to truncated and corrupted data.

### **Analysis of the Bug**

The root cause is that the CSV import logic was treating every comma as a column separator, even when it was inside quoted text. For a question like `"A and B..., B and C..."`, the parser would see the comma after "days" and incorrectly start a new column, which is why only the last part of the text was being saved.

### **The Permanent Fix**

I have replaced the faulty import logic with a robust, state-aware CSV parser. This new function correctly understands quoted fields and will ignore commas that are part of the question text itself. This ensures that your questions are imported fully and accurately, no matter how complex they are.

As per your specific instruction, I have only fixed this import issue and will provide the single, updated file below.

